Durban - A fire broke out in the Shaik Omar Trust building at the corner of Victoria (Bertha Mkhize) Street and Fishmarket Street after 8pm on Friday evening.

On arrival Durban central firemen found three rooms on fire. 
Firefighters managed to contain the fire to the second floor and the building was evacuated with no injuries reported. 
According to a report from Durban Central fire station, it is alleged that a traditional healer was burning medicine and left the room unattended which led to the fire breaking out. AdChoicesADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads
SAPS and Metro Police were on scene but confirm that no case was opened with the police. 

The building is currently being repaired with a fresh coat of paint and new windows already installed.